Body length 2.0–2.4. Dorsum generally dark brown. Pronotum slightly longer than median head length, with two transverse yellow stripes on anterior part. Hemelytron (
Fig. 5B
) with yellowish brown background and longitudinal yellowish stripes usually fragmented into small dots; embolium with three translucent patches.

Males: fore femur with a pair of spines on proximal third ventrally; fore tibia without spine (
Fig. 6E
); palar claw, median lobe of sternite VII and free lobe (
Fig. 6F
) as in diagnosis for subgenus. Left paramere: shaft slender, basally straight and curved at distal fourth; basal lobe broad, trapezoid (
Fig. 6H
). Right paramere: shaft broadly curved, distal half strongly broadened (
Fig. 6G
).

Vietnam : Ninh Binh (Cuc Phuong) ( Wróblewski 1967 ); first records for Cao Bang , Phu Tho , Hanoi , Thanh Hoa , Nghe An , Dong Nai . Other countries: southwestern China , Thailand , Indonesia , Peninsular Malaysia , Cambodia ( Lundblad 1933b ; Nieser 2000 , 2002b ;
Nieser et al. 2005
; Polhemus 2017 ).
